sql:
SELECT COUNT(student_id) 
FROM course_enrollment 
WHERE term_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'ME' in course codes typically stands for Mechanical Engineering; 
- Diligent students are those who attend more than 90% of the classes, indicating high attendance;
- The diligent students' performance is reflected through their total scores in the courses.

sql:
SELECT f.faculty_name, c.course_name 
FROM faculty f 
LEFT JOIN courses c ON f.faculty_id = c.instructor_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'blossomed into stars' refers to students who have excelled academically;
- 'guiding lights' refers to their instructors or faculty members;
- 'seasons of brilliance' refers to the terms during which they performed exceptionally;
- 'numeric ratings' correspond to their grade points;
- 'endured' is a metaphor for the attendance percentage;
- 'second chance' is a metaphor for a makeup exam;
- 'starlight' exceeding 4 means the grade point is greater than 4;
- 'part of the constellation' implies their enrollment status is active.

- "Identities" refers to the full names of the students;
- "Courses they attended" indicates that the query is interested in courses for which the students have performance data;
- "Terms during which these courses were taken" mean the instructional periods when the courses were completed;
- "Total scores" are the sum of all points obtained by the student in a course;
- "Letter grades" represent the symbolic representation of the student's performance, such as A+, B-, etc.;
- "Whether the grades were considered passing" means an indication of whether the grade the student received meets the passing criteria, typically denoted by 'is_pass' status.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT student_id)
FROM student_performance
WHERE grade_point >= 5 AND term_id = 1;

